      "body" : "So, I know this is over a decade old now, but I&#39;m brushing up on my java, and I just ran into a &quot;well technically ...&quot; situation wrt this.  Actually somewhat related to @Collin&#39;s comment.  If you are evaluating <code>a&amp;=booleanMethod()</code>, it is not strictly equivalent to <code>a=a&amp;&amp;booleanMethod()</code>, because if <code>a==false</code>, it won&#39;t evaluate <code>booleanMethod</code>.   So you&#39;d have to do <code>a=booleanMethod() &amp;&amp; a</code>."
