      "body" : "@MiaoLiu - That is what this is saying:  <i>&quot;There is only a semantic difference when <code>b</code> is a subexpression that has side-effects. In the <code>&amp;</code> case, the side-effect always occurs. In the <code>&amp;&amp;</code> case it occurs depending on the value of <code>a</code>.&quot;</i>   The &quot;<i>subexpression <code>b</code></i>&quot; would be a call to your <code>booleanMethod</code>.  (If <code>booleanMethod</code> doesn&#39;t have any side-effects then this is moot; i.e. no difference at all between <code>&amp;</code> and <code>&amp;&amp;</code> from a semantic perspective.)"
    } ],
