    "body" : "<p>Here's a simple way to test it:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public class OperatorTest {     \n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        boolean a = false;\n        a &amp;= b();\n    }\n\n    private static boolean b() {\n        System.out.println(\"b() was called\");\n        return true;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The output is <code>b() was called</code>, therefore the right-hand operand is evaluated.</p>\n\n<p>So, as already mentioned by others,  <code>a &amp;= b</code> is the same as <code>a = a &amp; b</code>.</p>\n"
  } ],
