  "title" : "Does the Java &amp;= operator apply &amp; or &amp;&amp;?",
  "body" : "<p>Assuming</p>\n\n<pre><code>boolean a = false;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I was wondering if doing:</p>\n\n<pre><code>a &amp;= b; \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>is equivalent to</p>\n\n<pre><code>a = a &amp;&amp; b; //logical AND, a is false hence b is not evaluated.\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or on the other hand it means</p>\n\n<pre><code>a = a &amp; b; //Bitwise AND. Both a and b are evaluated.\n</code></pre>\n"
}